verbose_text: Compared with progesterone, dydrogesterone has a greater affinity for the progesterone receptors and can be used at lower oral doses to promote endometrial proliferation, owing to its better bioavailability and to the progestogenic activity of its metabolites.
evidence: dydrogesterone has a greater affinity for the progesterone receptors and can be used at lower oral doses to promote endometrial proliferation
